# Plugin Spec Naming

Use one plugin spec per file.

Filename format
`<type>-<plugin>.lua`

`type`
2-letter category prefix
natural sort key

`plugin`
stable lowercase slug
usually repo name
use `-` separators

Prefix map
`aa` local config/session/bootstrap helpers
`ab` base/general utilities
`ai` AI assistants and completion
`la` language and filetype-specific plugins
`lz` LSP diagnostics completion coding infra
`ui` themes statusline picker visual UI
`wt` task/workflow/time plugins
`ww` writing/focus/prose workflow
`xx` general apps/navigation/misc

UI theme convention
Use `ui-theme-...` for theme/colorscheme plugins.
Use `ui-...` for non-theme UI plugins.

Rules
Keep exactly one active plugin spec per `.lua` file.
Preserve the same `type` prefix when splitting files.
Keep related config (`opts`, `config`, `keys`, `ft`, `cmd`, dependencies) in that plugin file.
Disable files with `.disable` suffix instead of deleting when archiving.

Examples
`ab-overseer.lua`
`la-vim-pandoc.lua`
`lz-trouble.lua`
`ui-theme-kanagawa.lua`
`wt-taskwiki.lua`
